  "prompt": "I told a girl in a relationship that I liked her and she says she never know what's going to happen to her relationship. What does that mean?",
  "response": "When someone says they \"don't know what's going to happen\" in their current relationship, it could mean several things:\n\n1. They might be experiencing problems or uncertainty in their current relationship\n2. They are considering ending their current relationship\n3. They are keeping their options open\n4. They might be interested in you but not ready to take action\n5. They could be trying to let you down gently without directly rejecting you\n\nWithout more context, it's hard to pinpoint exactly what she means. The most important things to remember are:\n- She is currently in a relationship\n- It would be unethical to pursue her while she's committed to someone else\n- Respect her current relationship and give her space\n\nThe healthiest approach is to maintain boundaries and not pursue her while she's with someone else.",
